âœ… Legal Usage (Inner Class)
class Bank {
    private class Account {
        void details() {
            System.out.println("Account details");
        }
    }
    void show() {
        Account acc = new Account();
        acc.details();
    }
}
ðŸ§  Meaning of private class
Accessible only inside the outer class
Hidden from other classes
Used for internal helper logic

